Unidentified man is captured in video claiming to be Army infantryman . 
 He's confronted by a young man who asks a series of questions including where he did basic training and why he's not wearing a name badge . 
 The man says he did basic training in North Carolina but the young man says infantry training is conducted in Fort Benning, Georgia not Miami . 
 Eric Coins, who posted the video, says the guy wore the uniform 'to pick up girls and get sympathy drinks'